The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Balaji has ?open mind?

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Lakshmipathy Balaji is sad for India not winning in Mohali, but is happy about his his performance. 

?This is one of my best performances,? Balaji said after reaching the city Sunday evening. ?I have never played at the Eden. I am going in with an open mind. It will be great if we can win here,? Balaji said. 

Virender Sehwag, Yuvraj Singh, Ashis Nehra and Gautam Gambhir, however, will reach he city on Monday. 

Pakistan manager Saleem Altaf, incidentally, was looking at Sehwag. ?Sehwag, on his day, can tear apart any bowler. Getting him early, along with Sachin Tendulkar and Rahul Dravid is important for the team.? 

The manager, confirmed that Shoaib Akhtar will not be able to take part in this series. 

Meanwhile, in a nice gesture the Pakistan team has agreed to grace a fund-raiser on Monday night in aid of the tsunami vicims I the Andaman and Nicobar Islands. 

The function, at the team hotel itself is being organised by an NGO ? Together, We Will. 




